The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems and algorithms, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of diversity is also closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as it involves finding a diverse set of solutions rather than just one optimal solution. The paper also mentions dynamic programming, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, and thus could be classified under cs.LG. Additionally, the paper discusses the translation of kernels, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
